      "writtenOn": "2021-02-10T09:24:50Z",
      "side": 0,
      "message": "Maybe to explain a bit more. Pre C++17 the instantiation was necessary and the compiler emitted a linker symbol. With C++17 the instantiation is obsolete, but still allowed. Compiler is free to ignore it. Clang still emits the linker symbol. However, GCC ignores it. Since Skia is compiled with C++17, GCC does not emit a linker symbol and therefore linking fails with undefined references. This is by the way independent of gold/bfd/lld. For demonstration see https://godbolt.org/z/ahddMv",
      "parentUuid": "4a223d04_98e3dc8f",
      "revId": "480d950d3c3a3761e51a04f3851c4d26bb675f1c",
